      <div class="responsive-bottom-margin">
          
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>This collection page brings together coronavirus guidance for DCMS sectors on gov.uk and partner websites.</p>

<div role="note" aria-label="Important" class="advisory">
<p><strong>National restrictions begin in England from 5 November. Find out about the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/new-national-restrictions-from-5-november?priority-taxon=774cee22-d896-44c1-a611-e3109cce8eae" class="govuk-link">new restrictions and what you can and cannot do</a>. Until 5 November, follow the local restrictions for your area.</strong></p>
</div>

<h2 id="guidance-published-on-partner-websites-that-dcms-has-contributed-to">Guidance published on partner websites that DCMS has contributed to:</h2>

<p>Association of Event Organisers: <a rel="external" href="https://www.aeo.org.uk/covid-19" class="govuk-link">COVID-19 Guidance for event recovery</a></p>

<p>bacta: <a rel="external" href="https://bacta.org.uk/2020/07/04/covid-19-updated-guidance/" class="govuk-link">Covid-19 updated guidance</a></p>

<p>The Betting and Gaming Council: <a rel="external" href="https://bettingandgamingcouncil.com/news/green-light-for-casinos-to-reopen-england/" class="govuk-link">COVID-19</a></p>

<p>The Bingo Association: <a rel="external" href="https://www.bingo-association.co.uk/coronaviruscovid-19" class="govuk-link">Coronavirus: COVID-19</a></p>

<p>British Association of Leisure Parks, Piers, and Amusements: <a rel="external" href="https://www.balppa.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Indoor-Play-Areas-for-Children-Operational-Guidance-for-Soft-Play-Equipment-Version-2-updated-on-01.10.2020.pdf" class="govuk-link">Indoor play areas for children operational guidance for soft play equipment</a></p>

<p>British Film Commission: <a rel="external" href="http://britishfilmcommission.org.uk/guidance/regarding-covid-19-coronavirus/" class="govuk-link">Coronavirus COVID-19 Guidance</a></p>

<p>Events Industry Forum: <a rel="external" href="https://www.eventsindustryforum.co.uk/index.php/11-features/14-keeping-workers-and-audiences-safe-during-covid-19" class="govuk-link">Keeping workers and audiences safe during COVID-19 in the Outdoor Event Industry in England</a></p>

<p>Fundraising Regulator: <a rel="external" href="https://www.fundraisingregulator.org.uk/more-from-us/coronavirus-advice" class="govuk-link">Coronavirus advice for fundraising organisations</a></p>

<p>Libraries Connected: <a rel="external" href="https://www.librariesconnected.org.uk/news/new-guide-help-libraries-reopen" class="govuk-link">Library recovery toolkit - June 2020</a></p>

<p>National Museums Directors’ Council (NMDC): <a rel="external" href="https://www.nationalmuseums.org.uk/coronavirus-update/nmdc-good-practice-guidelines-opening-museums/" class="govuk-link">Good Practice Guidelines on Opening Museums After 4 July</a></p>

<p>National Youth Agency: <a rel="external" href="https://nya.org.uk/guidance/" class="govuk-link">NYA COVID-19 Guidance</a></p>

<p>UK broadcasters: <a rel="external" href="https://downloads.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/tv-production-guidance-managing-the-risk-of-coronavirus-in-production-making-v1.pdf" class="govuk-link">TV Production Guidance: Managing the risk of Coronavirus (COVID-19) in production making</a></p>

<p>UK Cinema Association: <a rel="external" href="https://www.cinemauk.org.uk/coronavirus-covid-19/guidance-for-cinemas/" class="govuk-link">Cinemas - keeping workers and customers safe during COVID-19</a></p>

<p>UK Cinema Association: <a rel="external" href="https://www.cinemauk.org.uk/coronavirus-covid-19/guidance-for-cinemas//" class="govuk-link">Drive-in and other outdoor cinemas - keeping workers and customers safe during COVID-19</a></p>

<p>UK Hospitality: <a rel="external" href="https://www.ukhospitality.org.uk/page/UKHospitalityGuidanceforHospitality" class="govuk-link">COVID-19 secure guidelines for hospitality businesses</a></p>

<p>UK Music: <a rel="external" href="https://www.ukmusic.org/covid-19/guidance" class="govuk-link">Official Back To Work Guidance for Workplaces for Music & Music Video Production</a></p>

<p>UK Screen Alliance: <a rel="external" href="https://www.ukscreenalliance.co.uk/campaigns/guidance-for-safe-working-in-post-production-and-vfx-during-the-covid-19-pandemic/" class="govuk-link">Guidance for safe working in post-production and VFX during the COVID-19 pandemic</a></p>

</div>
</div>


